definition: to open/to start/to turn on/to boil/to write out (a prescription, check, invoice etc)/to operate (a vehicle)/carat (gold)/abbr. for Kelvin, 開爾文|开尔文[Kai1 er3 wen2]/abbr. for 開本|开本[kai1 ben3], book format
surname Yin/abbr. for 印度[Yin4 du4]
to print/to mark/to engrave/a seal/a print/a stamp/a mark/a trace/image

sentences.english: The paper went to bed at four this morning.
sentences.chinese: 報紙今天早上四點開印的。

sentences.english: How does America get more money? It merely prints it. I wish I could do that.
sentences.chinese: 美國如何搞到錢？開印就行了。我很想幹這活。
